# João Albuquerque Portfolio — Development Guidelines

Auto-generated from feature plan `001-visual-identity-github`. Last updated: 2026-03-12

## Active Technologies

- **TypeScript 5** (strict mode) — all component and data files
- **Next.js 14.2** (App Router) — framework
- **Tailwind CSS 3.4** — all styling; custom tokens in `tailwind.config.ts`
- **lucide-react 0.441** — ONLY icon library permitted
- **Inter** (next/font/google) — primary font

## Project Structure

```text
portfolio/
├── app/           ← Next.js App Router (layout, page, globals.css)
├── components/    ← One file per UI section; max 200 lines each
├── lib/data.ts    ← Single source of truth for ALL content
├── public/        ← Static assets (profile.jpg)
└── .specify/      ← Spec, plan, research, data-model artifacts
```

## Commands

```bash
npm run dev      # development server → http://localhost:3000
npm run build    # production build (must pass zero errors)
npm run lint     # ESLint check
```

## Code Style

- TypeScript strict — no `any`, no `// @ts-ignore`
- All data in `lib/data.ts` — components are pure/data-agnostic
- Icons: lucide-react only — no other icon library
- Colors: `#050505` bg, off-white text, `#10B981` (emerald) + `#06B6D4` (cyan) accents
- GitHub handle: `J-Albertoo` (two o's) — never `J-Alberto0` (with zero)
- `isPrivate: true` repos → render "Repo Privado" badge, NOT a link to profile

## Recent Changes

- `001-visual-identity-github`: TypeScript + Next.js 14 + Tailwind CSS + lucide-react
  - Corrected GitHub handle to `J-Albertoo` across all files
  - Added `NeuralDecoration` (desktop) + `MobileNeuralDots` (mobile) in Hero
